fields.description:
A user with read-only access receives an unclear message when they are not allowed to create a stack.  The following error message is displayed when attempting to create a stack.  More specifically, it happens when the user attempts to use any CF template.
{code}
Cannot create S3 bucket to store your CloudFormation template due to namespace collision. Please contact your cloud administrator.
{code}
I'm guessing this is because the user does not have access to create a stack.
